{{Infobox MP | honorific-suffix = | name = Alamgir Khan | office = Member of the [[National Assembly of Pakistan]] | term_start = 29 October 2018 | term_end = |constituency= [[NA-243 (Karachi East-II)]] | birth_date = | birth_place = |nationality = Pakistani |party = [[Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf]] }}
'''Alamgir Khan''' is a Pakistani activist turned politician who has been a member of the [[National Assembly of Pakistan]] since October 2018.
== Activism == While pursuing an MBA degree from [[Iqra University]], he started a campaign in January 2016 to spray-paint the portrait of then Chief Minister of Sindh [[Qaim Ali Shah]] alongside uncovered sewer holes and garbage dumps in various part of Karachi.<ref>{{cite news |title=In full swing: 42 manholes covered in Karachi's 'sleeping beauty' campaign {{!}} The Express Tribune |url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1024663/in-full-swing-42-manholes-covered-in-karachis-sleeping-beauty-campaign/ |accessdate=14 October 2018 |work=The Express Tribune |date=9 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Zahra |first1=Afshan |title=Alamgir Khan's #FixIt campaign in full swing |url=https://aaj.tv/2016/01/alamgir-khans-fixit-campaign-in-full-swing/ |accessdate=14 October 2018 |work=Aaj News}}</ref> The campaign called ''Fix It'' took social media by storm<ref>{{cite news |title=Power of an image: CM's face fills the gap where govt is missing {{!}} The Express Tribune |url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1021940/power-of-an-image-cms-face-fills-the-gap-where-govt-is-missing/ |accessdate=14 October 2018 |work=The Express Tribune |date=4 January 2016}}</ref><ref name="tribune/14jan2016">{{cite news |title=#Fixit |url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1027140/fixit/ |accessdate=14 October 2018 |work=The Express Tribune |date=14 January 2016}}</ref> which made Khan rose to fame.<ref name="dawn/18march2016"/>
On 25 February 2016, he was arrested by the police after he attempted to empty the garbage bins outside the Sindh Chief Minister House in Karachi.<ref>{{cite news |title=#FixIt campaigner Alamgir arrested in Karachi {{!}} The Express Tribune |url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1054309/police-arrest-fixit-campaigner-in-karachi/ |accessdate=14 October 2018 |work=The Express Tribune |date=25 February 2016}}</ref> The next day, he was released on bail.<ref>{{cite news |title=Fix-It campaigner Alamgir Khan released on bail |url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/101200-Fix-It-campaigner-Alamgir-Khan-released-on-bail |accessdate=14 October 2018 |work=The News |language=en}}</ref> In March 2016, a city court in Karachi indicted him in a case of wrongful restraint.<ref name="tribune/18march2016">{{cite news |title=#FixIt campaigner Alamgir Khan indicted {{!}} The Express Tribune |url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1068125/fixit-campaigner-alamgir-khan-indicted/ |accessdate=14 October 2018 |work=The Express Tribune |date=18 March 2016}}</ref><ref name="dawn/18march2016">{{cite news |last1=Tanoli |first1=Ishaq |title=&#039;Fix it&#039; campaigner Alamgir Khan indicted |url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1246465 |accessdate=14 October 2018 |work=DAWN.COM |date=18 March 2016}}</ref>
==Political career== In August 2018, he was allocated [[Pakistan Tehreek-e-Insaf]] (PTI) ticket to contest the by-election from Constituency [[NA-243 (Karachi East-II)]].<ref>{{cite news |title=FixIt founder set to contest Karachi by-poll on PTI ticket {{!}} The Express Tribune |url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/1771166/1-fixit-founder-hopeful-contest-karachi-poll-pti-ticket/ |accessdate=14 October 2018 |work=The Express Tribune |date=1 August 2018}}</ref>
He was elected to the [[National Assembly of Pakistan]] as a candidate of PTI from Constituency NA-243 (Karachi East-II) in by-election held on 14 October 2018.<ref>{{cite news |title=PTI's Alamgir wins NA-243 with big margin |url=https://nation.com.pk/15-Oct-2018/pti-s-alamgir-wins-na-243-with-big-margin |accessdate=15 October 2018 |work=The Nation |date=15 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Chaudhry |first1=Fahad |title=ECP notifies victory of 22 candidates, withholds notices of 13 others for not disclosing campaign costs |url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1439824/ecp-notifies-victory-of-22-candidates-withholds-notices-of-13-others-for-not-disclosing-campaign-costs |accessdate=19 October 2018 |work=DAWN.COM |date=18 October 2018}}</ref>
