'''BOLDfest (Bold Older Lesbians and Dykes)''' is an annual conference held in [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]] to create community for [[lesbian]]s over 45 from [[Canada]] and the [[United States]]. The conference is held by BOLD, a non-profit society, which states that its mission is "to raise the visibility of older lesbians, and to provide a venue to meet and to share information and opportunities for learning, networking, and organizing".<ref>{{cite web|title=About BOLDfest|url=http://www.boldfest.com/about.php|website=www.boldfest.com|accessdate=2016-12-13}}</ref> BOLDfest was created to create community for older lesbians, combat isolation and age-based exclusion from other facets of the [[LGBT community|queer community]], and to remember and celebrate lesbian histories.<ref>{{cite web|title=8th annual BOLD festival for older lesbians|url=http://dailyxtra.com/vancouver/news/8th-annual-bold-festival-older-lesbians-3601|website=dailyxtra.com|accessdate=12 January 2015}}</ref><ref name="Takeuchi">{{cite news|url=https://www.straight.com/blogra/boldfest-2012-honour-bold-voices-north-american-lesbians|title=BOLDFest 2012 to honour the bold voices of North American lesbians|last=Takeuchi|first=Craig|date=4 September 2012|work=[[Georgia Straight]]|accessdate=14 January 2015}}</ref>
BOLD was founded in 2004 by Pat Hogan and Claire Robson, and the annual conference is held in West Vancouver at the West Coast Plaza hotel on the weekend following [[Labour Day]] weekend. The annual gathering features workshops, dances, musical performances, and an array of social events. BOLD also features an award for BOLD Woman of the Year, honouring one woman from the North American lesbian community who has made significant contributions and who is underrepresented by the mainstream media.<ref>{{cite web|title=Older lesbians gather for 10th BOLD festival in Vancouver|url=http://dailyxtra.com/vancouver/news/older-lesbians-gather-10th-bold-festival-in-vancouver-92543|website=dailyxtra.com|accessdate=12 January 2015}}</ref> In 2014, BOLD celebrated their 10-year anniversary and honoured Margy Lesher, cofounder of [[Lesbian Connection|The Lesbian Connection]], the longest running worldwide lesbian publication, as BOLD Woman of the Year.<ref>{{cite web|title=More than 100 attend BOLDfest|url=http://dailyxtra.com/vancouver/news/100-attend-boldfest-69268|website=www.dailyxtra.com|accessdate=12 January 2015}}</ref> Over the years, BOLD has held a number of larger panel discussions during the conference, featuring many prominent lesbian and queer scholars, activists, and figures.<ref>{{cite web|title=BOLDFest 2012 to honour the bold voices of North American lesbians|url=https://www.straight.com/blogra/boldfest-2012-honour-bold-voices-north-american-lesbians|website=www.straight.com|accessdate=12 January 2015}}</ref>
