'''William E. Allen''' was an acting director of the [[United States|U.S.]] [[Bureau of Investigation]] (BOI) during 1919. The BOI was a predecessor of the [[Federal Bureau of Investigation]] (FBI).<ref name="fbi" />

A former assistant in war matters to the chief of the Bureau of Investigation, Allen was appointed acting director on February 10, 1919.<ref name="fbi" /> Allen resigned the post from June 30, 1919, and was replaced by [[William J. Flynn]].<ref name="fbi" />

